# Tips

**Focus on reference tokens**: Use `--reference-*` tokens for bibliography-specific customizations. These integrate with the design system while providing reference-specific control.

**Hanging indents require matching padding**: When using negative `--reference-text-indent` values, always set `--reference-padding-left` to the matching positive value to prevent text overflow.

**Combine tokens thoughtfully**: Dense bibliographies work well with `--space-3` spacing, `var(--font-size-sm)` font size, and optional hanging indents.

**Choose alignment for context**: Use `--reference-text-align: left` for most contexts, `justify` for traditional scholarly papers with hyphenation enabled.

**Consider hyphenation with justification**: Enable `--reference-hyphens: auto` when using justified text to prevent awkward spacing.

**Leverage semantic integration**: Reference spacing uses `--content-spacing` automatically, providing responsive and print behavior without explicit CSS. Override for special layouts only.

**Modern text wrapping**: Use `--reference-text-wrap: pretty` in supported browsers for improved line breaking, especially with long URLs or DOIs.

**Print optimization**: References automatically prevent page breaks within individual entries using `break-inside: avoid`. Adjust `--reference-orphans` and `--reference-widows` for additional control.

**Test with real content**: Verify reference styling with actual citations including long author lists, titles, journal names, and DOI/URL strings.